# Cursor Rules for React Native Expo Project

## React Native Expo Best Practices
- Use functional components with hooks
- Utilize Expo SDK features and APIs
- Implement proper navigation using React Navigation
- Use Expo's asset system for images and fonts
- Implement proper error handling and crash reporting
- Utilize Expo's push notification system

## File Structure
```
assets/
src/
  components/
  screens/
  navigation/
  hooks/
  utils/
App.js
app.json
```

## File Pattern Rules

### TypeScript Files (`**/*.ts`)
- Use TypeScript
- Enforce strict type checking
- Avoid using `any` type
- Implement proper type definitions

### TypeScript React Files (`**/*.tsx`)
- Use functional components
- Implement hooks
- Define proper prop types
- Avoid class components
- Use proper imports

### Style Files (`**/*.css`)
- Use Tailwind classes
- Avoid inline styles

### Test Files (`**/*.test.ts`)
- Write unit tests
- Use proper test descriptions

### Component Files (`src/components/**/*.tsx`)
- Follow single responsibility principle
- Implement proper error handling
- Include proper loading states
- Ensure proper accessibility

### Hook Files (`src/hooks/**/*.ts`)
- Use 'use' prefix for hook names
- Implement proper error handling
- Define proper type definitions

### Navigation Files (`src/navigation/**/*.tsx`)
- Use proper navigation types
- Implement proper navigation structure

### Asset Files (`src/assets/**/*`)
- Optimize images
- Use proper file formats

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase
- Hooks: camelCase with 'use' prefix
- Utilities: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Types: PascalCase

## Performance Guidelines
- Use proper list virtualization
- Implement proper memoization
- Optimize images
- Use proper caching strategies

## Security Guidelines
- Never include sensitive data in code
- Implement proper authentication
- Validate all input
- Use environment variables for sensitive data

